id: pm-hq28
title: Replace obsolete front-matter vocabulary with item metadata terminology
description: "Rename live code, APIs, identifiers, files, tests, diagnostics, documentation, generated compatibility fixtures, and review automation references away from frontmatter/front-matter/front_matter now that TOON is canonical. Preserve .agents/pm item files and history unchanged as historical evidence, retain legacy JSON-markdown compatibility behavior under accurate metadata-block terminology, and prove the repository has no tracked non-history occurrences."
type: Task
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[5]: developer-experience,metadata,refactor,toon,vocabulary
created_at: "2026-07-12T20:24:28.207Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-12T21:08:31.608Z"
assignee: codex-frontmatter-vocabulary
author: codex-frontmatter-vocabulary
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-12T20:42:43.447Z",codex-frontmatter-vocabulary,"Implementation evidence before external review: renamed the canonical item type and APIs to ItemMetadata/listAllItemMetadata/normalizeItemMetadata; renamed the cache module and test file to item-metadata-cache; updated CLI, SDK, package runtimes, tests, fixtures, import-boundary baseline, diagnostics, and TOON-specific prose; removed the obsolete ItemFrontMatter compatibility alias; retained splitFrontMatter plus YAML/JSON front-matter wording only where the files genuinely contain front matter; added scripts/reviews/pr-review-loop.mjs and docs/PR_REVIEW_LOOP.md for complete thread/reaction inventory and acknowledgements. Verification passed: pnpm build; focused 74-test item format/cache/record suite; full node scripts/run-tests.mjs test; full coverage; pnpm quality:static; pnpm quality:docs-skills; git diff --check; node --check review helper."
  "2026-07-12T20:50:50.050Z",codex-frontmatter-vocabulary,"Pre-push Greptile attempt evidence: review 84e236fa-46b4-4529-95fb-b0c3b21573cd was dispatched against main and allowed three uninterrupted five-minute windows, then failed unexpectedly without returning findings. This is an external reviewer failure, not a clean review; retrying the same committed diff before push."
  "2026-07-12T20:55:16.991Z",codex-frontmatter-vocabulary,"Pre-push Greptile retry evidence: review 4e722269-603b-4468-aecc-845f5df4a177 was dispatched against the same committed main diff and given the full 20-minute maximum (7 + 7 + 6 minute uninterrupted windows). It also ended with Greptile's external 'review failed unexpectedly' result and returned no findings. Both local Greptile attempts were run before push but cannot be treated as approval; hosted Greptile review remains mandatory on the PR current head before merge."
  "2026-07-12T21:08:31.607Z",codex-frontmatter-vocabulary,"Hosted CI root-cause and remediation evidence: PR #531 Gates (static) showed published pm-changelog importing removed listAllFrontMatter. Updated package tracker pmc-4a7j and published pm-changelog 2026.7.12-1 via free GitHub Actions release run 29209033251; release checks, npm publish, Bun install verification, tag/main push, and GitHub release all passed. Re-running the failed pm-cli job against the corrected package."
